      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the breakdown of principal versus interest changes dramatically over the life of a mortgage. In the early years, a much larger portion of your monthly payment goes toward paying the bank's interest because the remaining loan balance is so high. As you pay down the principal, the amount of interest you owe each month shrinks, meaning a larger chunk of your fixed payment goes toward reducing the actual loan balance in later years.",
      "source": "target",
