      "content": "It is indeed a common feeling, as the interest component is intentionally front-loaded in amortizing loans like a 30-year fixed mortgage. The system is designed so that the debt is serviced over time, which means interest accrues on the outstanding balance. The only way to actively \"stop\" that early interest drain is by making extra principal payments, which directly reduces the balance faster and lowers future interest charges.",
